 a unique combination of practical valuation techniques with the most current thinking this book provides readers with an uptodate synthesis of valuation theory as it applies to mergers buyouts and restructuring readers will gain a strong understanding of the problems encountered in valuation practice as well as sound solutions this includes detailed discussions of free cash flow valuation financing and valuation of leveraged buyouts real option analysis and much more book type educational material finance and commerce text book binding paperback language english number of pages  isbn –  x copyright year  the valuation for mergers buyouts and restructuring published on  resource for finance and commerce students and professionals table of contentsindexsyllabus of valuation for mergers buyouts and restructuring part one the tools of valuation · a user’s guide · forecasting and valuation of free cash flows · the equity premium and the cost of capital · metrics and multiples · economic value added · valuation with changing capital structure · debt capacity for acquisition financing · valuing entry and exit options part two mergers acquisitions and buyouts · mergers and acquisitions · deal making with difference of opinion · special offer structures price guarantees and collars · acquisitions in developed and emerging markets · leveraged buyouts part three recapitalizations and restructuring · recapitalization of troubled companies · asset restructuring appendix a financial options a financial options in m  a valuation a european calls and puts and american calls a american puts a warrant pricing model a asian options a knockout barrier options a the putcall parity a stock options paying a known dividend yield a dilution adjustment in warrant valuation problems appendix b valuation aids software appendix c answers to selected endofchapter problems appendix d modeling mergers and buyouts with dealmodeler user’s manual d brief description of dealmodeler d financial modeling d inputs d addictions d printing output d demo and blank copies d modeling mergers and acquisitions d setting up the financial model for ma transactions d valuation d checking the model d printing ma financials and valuation output d sensitivity and scenario analysis d modeling leveraged buyouts d setting up the financial model for lbo transactions d irr valuation d checking the model and printing technical notes references index about author of valuation for mergers buyouts and restructuring enrique arzac enrique arzac is professor of finance and economics at columbia university’s graduate school of business and director of the mergers and acquisition programs for senior executives offered at columbia business school and london business school previously he has served as chairman of the finance department and vice dean for academic affairs for the columbia graduate school of business he has published many articles on corporate finance portfolio management and commodity markets in the leading financial journals dr arzac is a director of the adams express company petroleum and resources corporation and bea funds in addition he has served as a financial consultant to the state of new jersey the united nations conference on trade development and several us and foreign firms and has lectured in numerous executive programs in north and south america and europe dr arzac holds a ma mba and phd all from columbia university salient features • language english • author arzac enrique rauthor • publisher wiley india pvt ltd about wiley india pvt ltdwse wiley india pvt ltdwse is a whollyowned subsidiary of john wiley  sons inc us listed on new york stock exchange with annual turnover of usd  billion wiley is a leading global publisher providing musthave content and services for the academic professional scientific technical medical scholarly and consumer markets wiley india pvt ltdwse is engaged in publishing and reprinting of worldclass books in the areas of science technolo